- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing tasks such as relation extraction and machine comprehension. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of machine learning models for relation extraction. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper discusses the transfer learning approach for cross-lingual relation extraction. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of multilingual resources for populating knowledge bases. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is less likely but still relevant as the paper discusses the use of neural network models for relation extraction.
